# regression_smoke.numos — open the Regression app, screenshot, and ASSERT it is active.
#
# Phase 7C smoke test. RegressionApp is LVGL-native and emulator-safe: it pulls only
# lvgl + ui::StatusBar + input/KeyCodes + KeyboardManager + a pure <cmath>
# RegressionEngine (least-squares; no Giac/CAS, no LittleFS/Preferences, no
# heap_caps/PSRAM, no sensors/WiFi; RegressionApp.cpp:25-28, RegressionEngine.cpp:26-27).
# This script opens it through the emulator-only `open_app` command (Phase 5A: it calls
# the SAME NativeHal launchApp() the launcher uses — id 6, the Regression card id, so it
# is deterministic and does not depend on fragile grid navigation), captures a screenshot,
# and asserts the active app is "Regression".
#
# The app opens on its "Data" tab showing a 2-column X/Y table with exactly one empty row
# (_numRows=1; RegressionApp.cpp:218-219). RegressionApp has NO update() method
# (RegressionApp.cpp:707-735) and no timer-driven cursor blink, so as with every emulator
# screen the only volatile region across runs is the StatusBar clock (HH:MM). This phase
# makes NO golden claim; the screenshot is a CANDIDATE for human review only (a clock mask
# is added by the human at promotion time, rect 4,6,37,13).
#
# Timing notes (deterministic, step-ms 16):
#   * 200 frames -> splash (~frame 125) is done; we are in the launcher.
#   * 60 frames  -> Regression screen load + 200ms fade settles after open_app.
#
# Run:
#   program --headless --deterministic --script tests/emulator/scripts/regression_smoke.numos \
#           --frames 800 --screenshot out/regression_smoke.ppm --quiet
# Exit codes: 0 ok · 2 script/parse error · 3 screenshot write error · 4 assertion failure.

log "regression_smoke: waiting for launcher"
wait 200

# Open Regression (emulator launchApp id 6 — same id as the launcher's Regression card).
open_app Regression
wait 60

# Screenshot FIRST: the deferred capture happens on this frame, before the assert
# runs on a later frame, so the artifact is produced even if the assertion fails.
screenshot out/regression_smoke.ppm
log "regression_smoke: screenshot captured"

assert_app Regression
log "regression_smoke: assertion passed (Regression active)"
